1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,920
 (speaking in foreign language)

2
00:00:03,920 --> 00:00:16,800
 - Good morning, brothers and sisters.

3
00:00:16,800 --> 00:00:20,720
 (speaking in foreign language)

4
00:00:20,720 --> 00:00:25,240
 Sorry, let's read Ephesians 3, 7 to 13.

5
00:00:25,240 --> 00:00:28,400
 (speaking in foreign language)

6
00:00:28,400 --> 00:00:32,320
 (speaking in foreign language)

7
00:00:55,280 --> 00:00:58,120
 Of this gospel, I was made a minister

8
00:00:58,120 --> 00:01:01,080
 according to the gift of God's grace,

9
00:01:01,080 --> 00:01:04,440
 which was given me by the working of his power.

10
00:01:04,440 --> 00:01:08,360
 To me, though I am the very least of all the saints,

11
00:01:08,360 --> 00:01:12,720
 this grace was given to preach to the Gentiles

12
00:01:12,720 --> 00:01:15,720
 the unsearchable riches of Christ,

13
00:01:15,720 --> 00:01:17,960
 and to bring the light to everyone

14
00:01:17,960 --> 00:01:22,280
 what is planned of the mystery hidden for ages in God,

15
00:01:22,280 --> 00:01:24,520
 who created all things.

16
00:01:25,680 --> 00:01:29,600
 (speaking in foreign language)

17
00:01:29,600 --> 00:01:55,200
 So that through the church and the manifold

18
00:01:55,200 --> 00:01:58,880
 wisdom of God that might now be made known

19
00:01:58,880 --> 00:02:02,720
 to the rulers and authorities in the heavenly places.

20
00:02:02,720 --> 00:02:05,160
 This was according to the internal purpose

21
00:02:05,160 --> 00:02:10,000
 that he has realized in Christ Jesus our Lord,

22
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:14,000
 in whom we have boldness and access with confidence

23
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:15,680
 through our faith in him.

24
00:02:15,680 --> 00:02:19,280
 So I ask you not to lose heart over what I'm suffering

25
00:02:19,280 --> 00:02:21,560
 for you, which is your glory.

26
00:02:24,720 --> 00:02:28,640
 (speaking in foreign language)

27
00:02:28,640 --> 00:02:36,560
 And have you ever woke up in the middle of the night

28
00:02:36,560 --> 00:02:40,680
 with your full heart of fear and anxiety?

29
00:02:40,680 --> 00:02:44,600
 (speaking in foreign language)

30
00:02:53,320 --> 00:02:55,480
 So maybe you're worried about work,

31
00:02:55,480 --> 00:02:57,640
 maybe money, your health,

32
00:02:57,640 --> 00:03:00,200
 feeling like maybe you are not good enough,

33
00:03:00,200 --> 00:03:03,000
 scared about how people look at you

34
00:03:03,000 --> 00:03:05,160
 and maybe look down upon you.

35
00:03:05,160 --> 00:03:09,080
 (speaking in foreign language)

36
00:03:09,080 --> 00:03:13,440
 I've been there, I've been tried this before.

37
00:03:13,440 --> 00:03:15,720
 Sometimes I woke up in the middle of the night

38
00:03:15,720 --> 00:03:18,320
 in such pressure and then I'm even stressed out

39
00:03:18,320 --> 00:03:19,480
 in my dreams.

40
00:03:19,480 --> 00:03:23,240
 (speaking in foreign language)

41
00:03:24,320 --> 00:03:26,640
 A lot of people look strong and busy outside,

42
00:03:26,640 --> 00:03:29,840
 but deep down they are living in constant fear.

43
00:03:29,840 --> 00:03:33,760
 (speaking in foreign language)

44
00:03:51,360 --> 00:03:55,440
 We don't just fear about our consistence.

45
00:03:55,440 --> 00:03:58,280
 (speaking in foreign language)

46
00:03:58,280 --> 00:04:02,600
 And at the deepest level, people are actually afraid of God.

47
00:04:02,600 --> 00:04:07,040
 We know instinctively that God is holy and we are not.

48
00:04:07,040 --> 00:04:11,560
 After Adam sinned, his first reaction wasn't to run to God,

49
00:04:11,560 --> 00:04:13,520
 it was to hide from him.

50
00:04:13,520 --> 00:04:15,400
 People today do the same thing.

51
00:04:15,400 --> 00:04:18,960
 We use success and business to cover up the emptiness

52
00:04:18,960 --> 00:04:21,720
 of being separated from God.

53
00:04:21,720 --> 00:04:25,640
 (speaking in foreign language)

54
00:04:25,640 --> 00:04:37,240
 But there is the amazing part of gospel

55
00:04:37,240 --> 00:04:41,840
 is God doesn't wait for us to become worthy or perfect

56
00:04:41,840 --> 00:04:44,840
 before he lets us become close to him.

57
00:04:44,840 --> 00:04:47,440
 While we are still sinner,

58
00:04:47,440 --> 00:04:50,280
 Christ already opened the way for us.

59
00:04:50,280 --> 00:04:54,200
 (speaking in foreign language)

60
00:04:54,200 --> 00:05:06,960
 Ephesians 3, 7 to 13 shows us that a person

61
00:05:06,960 --> 00:05:10,040
 who used to tremble in fear before God

62
00:05:10,040 --> 00:05:14,160
 can now come to his presence with complete confidence

63
00:05:14,160 --> 00:05:17,600
 and it all because of Christ.

64
00:05:17,600 --> 00:05:21,520
 (speaking in foreign language)

65
00:05:21,520 --> 00:05:30,280
 Today, we will look at three things from this passage.

66
00:05:30,280 --> 00:05:32,640
 The number one thing that we will cover today

67
00:05:32,640 --> 00:05:36,200
 is by grace, no longer fear our unworthiness.

68
00:05:36,200 --> 00:05:40,120
 (speaking in foreign language)

69
00:05:45,160 --> 00:05:49,080
 (speaking in foreign language)

70
00:05:49,080 --> 00:05:58,880
 I became a servant of the gospel

71
00:05:58,880 --> 00:06:02,520
 according to the gift of God, of God's grace.

72
00:06:02,520 --> 00:06:06,120
 The word minister or servant in the original text

73
00:06:06,120 --> 00:06:10,720
 means a servant or a person who serves.

74
00:06:10,720 --> 00:06:15,040
 Paul did not begin by emphasizing I'm an apostle.

75
00:06:15,040 --> 00:06:19,640
 Instead, and a stress that he was a servant of the gospel

76
00:06:19,640 --> 00:06:22,160
 and this is very important because in ministry,

77
00:06:22,160 --> 00:06:26,400
 the greatest danger is not weakness, but pride.

78
00:06:26,400 --> 00:06:30,320
 (speaking in foreign language)

79
00:06:30,320 --> 00:06:37,200
 So Paul understood clearly that his ministry

80
00:06:37,200 --> 00:06:39,920
 was not based on his own qualification,

81
00:06:39,920 --> 00:06:42,960
 but on God's free and unmerited grace.

82
00:06:42,960 --> 00:06:46,880
 (speaking in foreign language)

83
00:06:46,880 --> 00:07:08,680
 Paul had once persecuted the church

84
00:07:08,680 --> 00:07:12,040
 and arrested Christian and was even glad

85
00:07:12,040 --> 00:07:15,040
 when Stephen was stoned to death.

86
00:07:15,040 --> 00:07:18,560
 Think about it, on the road of Damascus,

87
00:07:18,560 --> 00:07:23,040
 Paul was not going to worship God, but to arrest Christians.

88
00:07:23,040 --> 00:07:24,720
 He thought he was serving God,

89
00:07:24,720 --> 00:07:27,840
 but in reality, he was opposing him.

90
00:07:27,840 --> 00:07:31,760
 (speaking in foreign language)

91
00:07:38,000 --> 00:07:41,000
 But on that road, the rising Christ

92
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:43,160
 took the initiative to find him.

93
00:07:43,160 --> 00:07:44,680
 (speaking in foreign language)

94
00:07:44,680 --> 00:07:46,920
 Why are you persecuting me?

95
00:07:46,920 --> 00:07:50,840
 (speaking in foreign language)

96
00:07:50,840 --> 00:08:03,600
 Only then did Paul truly realize that he had been doing.

97
00:08:03,600 --> 00:08:05,440
 That is grace.

98
00:08:05,440 --> 00:08:08,720
 Grace is not man seeking God,

99
00:08:08,720 --> 00:08:12,160
 but God actively seeking and saving

100
00:08:12,160 --> 00:08:15,280
 those who were once his enemies.

101
00:08:15,280 --> 00:08:19,200
 (speaking in foreign language)

102
00:08:19,200 --> 00:08:31,080
 Paul said, "I am the very least of all the saints."

103
00:08:31,080 --> 00:08:34,120
 He was not pretending to be humble

104
00:08:34,120 --> 00:08:37,320
 or trying to put in on a spiritual show.

105
00:08:37,320 --> 00:08:42,280
 These are the words of someone who truly knew himself.

106
00:08:42,280 --> 00:08:46,200
 (speaking in foreign language)

107
00:08:46,200 --> 00:08:59,760
 Paul knew that if Christ had not stopped him on that road,

108
00:08:59,760 --> 00:09:03,400
 he would never ever have returned to God by himself.

109
00:09:03,400 --> 00:09:05,520
 The more he understood grace,

110
00:09:05,520 --> 00:09:08,520
 the more he realized how unworthy he was.

111
00:09:08,520 --> 00:09:12,440
 (speaking in foreign language)

112
00:09:12,440 --> 00:09:29,880
 Today, many Christians are constantly fixated

113
00:09:29,880 --> 00:09:32,160
 on their own unworthiness.

114
00:09:32,160 --> 00:09:34,160
 "My education is not good enough.

115
00:09:34,160 --> 00:09:35,960
 "I'm not eloquent.

116
00:09:35,960 --> 00:09:38,120
 "My life has too many problems."

117
00:09:38,120 --> 00:09:40,720
 They say, "When I become more mature,

118
00:09:40,720 --> 00:09:42,920
 "maybe one day I will serve.

119
00:09:42,920 --> 00:09:44,760
 "Or when I understand the Bible better,

120
00:09:44,760 --> 00:09:47,040
 "then I will got involved in church."

121
00:09:47,040 --> 00:09:50,960
 (speaking in foreign language)

122
00:10:01,920 --> 00:10:05,520
 But in the Bible, there was not even one single person

123
00:10:05,520 --> 00:10:09,760
 whom God used only after they have become perfect.

124
00:10:09,760 --> 00:10:13,680
 God does not use people because they are already complete,

125
00:10:13,680 --> 00:10:16,640
 but because Christ is complete.

126
00:10:16,640 --> 00:10:20,560
 (speaking in foreign language)

127
00:10:20,560 --> 00:10:23,520
 So God accepts unworthy people

128
00:10:23,520 --> 00:10:27,040
 and uses unworthy people in Christ.

129
00:10:27,040 --> 00:10:30,960
 (speaking in foreign language)

130
00:10:32,520 --> 00:10:36,440
 (speaking in foreign language)

131
00:10:36,440 --> 00:10:47,520
 So this passage also gives great hope

132
00:10:47,520 --> 00:10:49,320
 to those who have failed.

133
00:10:49,320 --> 00:10:52,520
 Some people feel, "I have failed too many times.

134
00:10:52,520 --> 00:10:54,920
 "I have let God down too much.

135
00:10:54,920 --> 00:10:57,160
 "God must have given up on me."

136
00:10:57,160 --> 00:10:59,560
 We believe God can forgive others,

137
00:10:59,560 --> 00:11:03,840
 but we find it hard to believe He will forgive us too.

138
00:11:03,840 --> 00:11:08,840
 (speaking in foreign language)

139
00:11:08,840 --> 00:11:23,920
 If God did not give up on a person like Paul,

140
00:11:23,920 --> 00:11:28,440
 then we today are not beyond His grace either.

141
00:11:28,440 --> 00:11:31,160
 The greatest hope for the gospel is this.

142
00:11:31,160 --> 00:11:34,760
 God saves not the pretty good people,

143
00:11:34,760 --> 00:11:36,520
 but the real sinners.

144
00:11:36,520 --> 00:11:41,800
 (speaking in foreign language)

145
00:11:41,800 --> 00:11:48,560
 So what truly makes us stand firm is not ourselves,

146
00:11:48,560 --> 00:11:50,600
 but the grace of Christ.

147
00:11:50,600 --> 00:11:54,520
 (speaking in foreign language)

148
00:11:59,440 --> 00:12:03,440
 By the cross, no longer living in separation.

149
00:12:03,440 --> 00:12:07,360
 (speaking in foreign language)

150
00:12:27,040 --> 00:12:29,600
 To preach to the Gentiles

151
00:12:29,600 --> 00:12:32,360
 the unsearchable riches of Christ,

152
00:12:32,360 --> 00:12:36,920
 these unsearchable riches do not refer

153
00:12:36,920 --> 00:12:40,120
 merely to material blessing,

154
00:12:40,120 --> 00:12:42,120
 but to God's salvation,

155
00:12:42,120 --> 00:12:44,440
 the forgiveness of sins,

156
00:12:44,440 --> 00:12:48,680
 sanctification, and presence of Christ.

157
00:12:48,680 --> 00:12:51,080
 Christ is not a poor savior.

158
00:12:51,080 --> 00:12:55,960
 He is a rich God, and what He gives is true abundance.

159
00:12:55,960 --> 00:12:59,360
 We may not lack material things,

160
00:12:59,360 --> 00:13:04,160
 but we often fail to enjoy the riches we have in Christ.

161
00:13:04,160 --> 00:13:08,080
 (speaking in foreign language)

162
00:13:08,080 --> 00:13:19,040
 Paul then speaks about mystery.

163
00:13:19,040 --> 00:13:20,800
 As mentioned before, this mystery

164
00:13:20,800 --> 00:13:23,240
 is not something mysterious,

165
00:13:23,240 --> 00:13:25,920
 but a truth that was hidden for ages

166
00:13:25,920 --> 00:13:28,840
 and has now been revealed.

167
00:13:28,840 --> 00:13:32,760
 (speaking in foreign language)

168
00:13:32,760 --> 00:13:37,760
 What is the truth?

169
00:13:37,760 --> 00:13:40,840
 The Gentiles and Jews become one body in Christ.

170
00:13:40,840 --> 00:13:44,760
 (speaking in foreign language)

171
00:13:44,760 --> 00:13:48,160
 We consider this quite normal today,

172
00:13:48,160 --> 00:13:51,680
 but in the first century, it was a shocking declaration.

173
00:13:51,680 --> 00:13:55,600
 (speaking in foreign language)

174
00:14:19,440 --> 00:14:21,840
 In the first century, there was a huge divide

175
00:14:21,840 --> 00:14:24,280
 between Jews and Gentiles.

176
00:14:24,280 --> 00:14:28,960
 Jews regarded Gentiles as unclean and far from God.

177
00:14:28,960 --> 00:14:32,280
 They were even unwilling to enter a Gentile's house.

178
00:14:32,280 --> 00:14:35,200
 Some Jew would rather take a long detour

179
00:14:35,200 --> 00:14:37,840
 than pass through Samaria.

180
00:14:37,840 --> 00:14:39,960
 For a Gentile to be saved,

181
00:14:39,960 --> 00:14:42,600
 they first have to become a Jew,

182
00:14:42,600 --> 00:14:45,440
 be circumcised, and keep the law.

183
00:14:46,880 --> 00:14:50,800
 (speaking in foreign language)

184
00:14:50,800 --> 00:15:07,360
 So there was a deep war between people,

185
00:15:07,360 --> 00:15:10,800
 a war of ethnicity, a war of culture,

186
00:15:10,800 --> 00:15:13,920
 a war of religion, and a war of identity.

187
00:15:13,920 --> 00:15:18,920
 But the cross demolished the dividing wall of hostility.

188
00:15:18,920 --> 00:15:24,440
 Those who were once enemies are now in Christ's one family.

189
00:15:24,440 --> 00:15:28,480
 (speaking in foreign language)

190
00:15:44,720 --> 00:15:48,640
 (speaking in foreign language)

191
00:15:48,640 --> 00:15:55,640
 The deeper meaning is found in verse 10.

192
00:15:55,640 --> 00:15:58,760
 God did this so that through the church

193
00:15:58,760 --> 00:16:01,680
 and the manifold wisdom of God

194
00:16:01,680 --> 00:16:04,240
 might now be made known to the rulers

195
00:16:04,240 --> 00:16:07,040
 and authorities in the heavenly places.

196
00:16:07,040 --> 00:16:12,040
 When a once proud Jew and a former idol-worshiping Gentiles

197
00:16:12,560 --> 00:16:15,280
 they worship together, love each other,

198
00:16:15,280 --> 00:16:17,520
 and serve each other in the church.

199
00:16:17,520 --> 00:16:20,400
 Even the angels are watching attentively

200
00:16:20,400 --> 00:16:22,720
 and exclaimingly in amazement.

201
00:16:22,720 --> 00:16:26,120
 This is the manifold wisdom of God.

202
00:16:26,120 --> 00:16:30,040
 (speaking in foreign language)

203
00:16:30,040 --> 00:16:39,400
 So church is no longer merely a religion organization.

204
00:16:39,440 --> 00:16:44,120
 It's a living testimony of God's redemptive wisdom

205
00:16:44,120 --> 00:16:46,360
 displayed in the universe.

206
00:16:46,360 --> 00:16:50,280
 (speaking in foreign language)

207
00:17:09,880 --> 00:17:13,720
 (speaking in foreign language)

208
00:17:13,720 --> 00:17:15,280
 Brothers and sisters,

209
00:17:15,280 --> 00:17:18,200
 this world is becoming increasingly divided

210
00:17:18,200 --> 00:17:23,200
 between nations, between ethnic groups, between individuals.

211
00:17:23,200 --> 00:17:24,920
 People attack each other

212
00:17:24,920 --> 00:17:28,120
 because of cultural and background differences.

213
00:17:28,120 --> 00:17:30,200
 There are conflicts everywhere.

214
00:17:30,200 --> 00:17:33,440
 Online, I myself used to argue

215
00:17:33,440 --> 00:17:38,000
 and even sometimes curse at others in the internet.

216
00:17:38,000 --> 00:17:40,040
 There are conflicts even at home

217
00:17:40,040 --> 00:17:42,320
 and it's becoming harder and harder

218
00:17:42,320 --> 00:17:44,640
 for people to trust one another.

219
00:17:44,640 --> 00:17:47,160
 But the church should be the place

220
00:17:47,160 --> 00:17:49,760
 where the world sees the gospel.

221
00:17:49,760 --> 00:17:53,680
 (speaking in foreign language)

222
00:18:04,360 --> 00:18:08,560
 The church is not a social club or interest group

223
00:18:08,560 --> 00:18:10,520
 where similar people gather.

224
00:18:10,520 --> 00:18:12,720
 The true church consists of people

225
00:18:12,720 --> 00:18:15,640
 who never naturally be together

226
00:18:15,640 --> 00:18:20,440
 yet have become one body because of Christ.

227
00:18:20,440 --> 00:18:24,360
 (speaking in foreign language)

228
00:18:32,280 --> 00:18:35,440
 There are people of different cultural backgrounds,

229
00:18:35,440 --> 00:18:39,120
 different levels of education, different personality,

230
00:18:39,120 --> 00:18:41,400
 yet because of Christ,

231
00:18:41,400 --> 00:18:44,200
 they accept one another and love each other.

232
00:18:44,200 --> 00:18:48,120
 (speaking in foreign language)

233
00:18:48,120 --> 00:18:58,720
 The world will ask, why can these people love each other?

234
00:18:58,720 --> 00:19:02,800
 The answer is not because they are all wonderful people,

235
00:19:02,800 --> 00:19:04,440
 but because of Christ.

236
00:19:04,440 --> 00:19:08,360
 (speaking in foreign language)

237
00:19:08,360 --> 00:19:17,640
 So when the church lives in such unity,

238
00:19:17,640 --> 00:19:22,640
 not only will this world see the reality of gospel,

239
00:19:22,640 --> 00:19:27,760
 even the rulers and authorities in the heavenly realms

240
00:19:27,760 --> 00:19:30,760
 will see the unsearchable wisdom of God.

241
00:19:30,760 --> 00:19:36,360
 (speaking in foreign language)

242
00:19:36,360 --> 00:19:41,080
 What truly unites us is not ourselves,

243
00:19:41,080 --> 00:19:42,920
 but the cross of Christ.

244
00:19:42,920 --> 00:19:47,840
 (speaking in foreign language)

245
00:19:47,840 --> 00:19:53,000
 By Christ, we can boldly come to the Father.

246
00:19:53,000 --> 00:19:56,920
 (speaking in foreign language)

247
00:19:58,120 --> 00:20:03,040
 Don't take this statement for granted today.

248
00:20:03,040 --> 00:20:04,840
 In Old Testament time,

249
00:20:04,840 --> 00:20:08,000
 people could not casually approach God.

250
00:20:08,000 --> 00:20:11,920
 (speaking in foreign language)

251
00:20:26,320 --> 00:20:29,200
 When God revealed himself on Mount Sinai,

252
00:20:29,200 --> 00:20:31,000
 everyone was terrified,

253
00:20:31,000 --> 00:20:35,240
 and only Moses was allowed to represent them before God.

254
00:20:35,240 --> 00:20:38,960
 Later, in the temple, only the high priests

255
00:20:38,960 --> 00:20:42,560
 could carefully enter the most holy place

256
00:20:42,560 --> 00:20:44,360
 to offer sacrifices,

257
00:20:44,360 --> 00:20:48,360
 because the sinner could not bear God's holiness.

258
00:20:48,360 --> 00:20:52,280
 (speaking in foreign language)

259
00:20:56,320 --> 00:21:00,240
 (speaking in foreign language)

260
00:21:00,240 --> 00:21:19,960
 But now, because of Jesus,

261
00:21:19,960 --> 00:21:23,280
 we can come boldly into God's presence.

262
00:21:23,280 --> 00:21:26,800
 This boldness is not because we have become worthy,

263
00:21:26,800 --> 00:21:30,400
 but because Jesus has accomplished everything.

264
00:21:30,400 --> 00:21:33,800
 Jesus' precious blood has removed our sins

265
00:21:33,800 --> 00:21:37,400
 and torn the veil of most holy place.

266
00:21:37,400 --> 00:21:39,120
 The book of Hebrews says,

267
00:21:39,120 --> 00:21:41,920
 "Let us then with confidence

268
00:21:41,920 --> 00:21:44,800
 "draw near to the throne of the grace.

269
00:21:44,800 --> 00:21:46,920
 "It's not by our good work,

270
00:21:46,920 --> 00:21:49,440
 "but by the merit of Christ."

271
00:21:50,600 --> 00:21:54,520
 (speaking in foreign language)

272
00:21:54,520 --> 00:22:08,360
 Many Christians still live in the state of hiding from God.

273
00:22:08,360 --> 00:22:12,840
 As soon as they sin, they will not pray.

274
00:22:12,840 --> 00:22:15,440
 Then when they become weak

275
00:22:15,440 --> 00:22:18,240
 and they start staying away from church meeting

276
00:22:18,240 --> 00:22:22,400
 because they feel God must be very disappointed in me.

277
00:22:22,400 --> 00:22:27,360
 (speaking in foreign language)

278
00:22:27,360 --> 00:22:39,040
 But gospel does not say you have no sin.

279
00:22:39,040 --> 00:22:42,960
 It says Christ has already borne your sin for you.

280
00:22:42,960 --> 00:22:45,680
 Therefore, today you do not come to God

281
00:22:45,680 --> 00:22:47,760
 based on your own performance,

282
00:22:47,760 --> 00:22:49,360
 but based on Christ.

283
00:22:49,360 --> 00:22:54,240
 (speaking in foreign language)

284
00:22:54,240 --> 00:23:06,640
 We can remain bold even in suffering.

285
00:23:06,640 --> 00:23:08,120
 Paul continues,

286
00:23:08,120 --> 00:23:11,400
 "So I ask you not to lose heart

287
00:23:11,400 --> 00:23:13,880
 "over what I'm suffering for you,

288
00:23:13,880 --> 00:23:15,840
 "which is your glory."

289
00:23:15,840 --> 00:23:19,760
 (speaking in foreign language)

290
00:23:46,840 --> 00:23:49,760
 At that time, Paul was in prison.

291
00:23:49,760 --> 00:23:52,480
 Yet instead of asking the Ephesian church

292
00:23:52,480 --> 00:23:54,160
 to feel sorry for him,

293
00:23:54,160 --> 00:23:57,800
 he said, "This suffering were their glory."

294
00:23:57,800 --> 00:23:58,800
 Why?

295
00:23:58,800 --> 00:24:01,080
 Because his suffering allowed the gospel

296
00:24:01,080 --> 00:24:06,040
 to reach Gentiles and God's mystery to be unfolded.

297
00:24:06,040 --> 00:24:09,440
 The world saw chains and shame,

298
00:24:09,440 --> 00:24:14,160
 but Paul saw God's glory and benefit of the church.

299
00:24:14,160 --> 00:24:18,080
 (speaking in foreign language)

300
00:24:18,080 --> 00:24:39,440
 This brings tremendous comfort to us today.

301
00:24:39,440 --> 00:24:43,400
 Many Christian easily become discouraged in trials.

302
00:24:43,400 --> 00:24:46,440
 Financial burdens, family problems,

303
00:24:46,440 --> 00:24:50,600
 difficulties at work, rebellious children,

304
00:24:50,600 --> 00:24:53,760
 health issues, so on.

305
00:24:53,760 --> 00:24:56,120
 We often ask, "God, why me?

306
00:24:56,120 --> 00:24:58,960
 "Why do others have so easy life

307
00:24:58,960 --> 00:25:01,240
 "while I struggle so much?"

308
00:25:01,240 --> 00:25:06,040
 (speaking in foreign language)

309
00:25:14,400 --> 00:25:18,400
 The gospel does not promise a smooth and easy life.

310
00:25:18,400 --> 00:25:22,120
 It promised us that even in the darkness trial,

311
00:25:22,120 --> 00:25:25,360
 we can still come boldly to our heavenly father.

312
00:25:25,360 --> 00:25:30,360
 (speaking in foreign language)

313
00:25:39,440 --> 00:25:43,600
 The sign of God's presence is not necessarily

314
00:25:43,600 --> 00:25:45,400
 a smooth environment,

315
00:25:45,400 --> 00:25:48,480
 but the presence of peace, hope,

316
00:25:48,480 --> 00:25:50,760
 and the ability to call on his name

317
00:25:50,760 --> 00:25:52,480
 even in the midst of hardship.

318
00:25:52,480 --> 00:25:57,280
 (speaking in foreign language)

319
00:26:10,440 --> 00:26:15,120
 True strength is not grinding our teeth

320
00:26:15,120 --> 00:26:17,480
 and enduring by ourselves,

321
00:26:17,480 --> 00:26:22,120
 but coming to God through Christ even in our weakness.

322
00:26:22,120 --> 00:26:24,960
 Just as Paul experienced in prison.

323
00:26:24,960 --> 00:26:27,280
 Often the most difficult times

324
00:26:27,280 --> 00:26:30,880
 become the times when we draw closest to God

325
00:26:30,880 --> 00:26:34,800
 and experience his great power most clearly.

326
00:26:34,800 --> 00:26:38,760
 (speaking in foreign language)

327
00:26:38,760 --> 00:26:41,320
 What truly makes us bold and fearless

328
00:26:41,320 --> 00:26:43,960
 is not ourselves, but Christ.

329
00:26:43,960 --> 00:26:48,800
 (speaking in foreign language)

330
00:27:09,600 --> 00:27:14,240
 (speaking in foreign language)

331
00:27:14,240 --> 00:27:15,960
 Brothers and sisters,

332
00:27:15,960 --> 00:27:20,280
 let's honestly ask ourselves this question today.

333
00:27:20,280 --> 00:27:24,400
 Am I still living in the fear of not being good enough,

334
00:27:24,400 --> 00:27:27,960
 afraid to serve or fully commit myself?

335
00:27:27,960 --> 00:27:30,560
 Am I still living in separation,

336
00:27:30,560 --> 00:27:33,320
 having barriers with brothers and sisters

337
00:27:33,320 --> 00:27:35,200
 or distance from God?

338
00:27:35,200 --> 00:27:39,200
 Am I still living in discouragement because of trials,

339
00:27:39,200 --> 00:27:42,680
 afraid of the future, afraid of my circumstance,

340
00:27:42,680 --> 00:27:45,040
 afraid I won't make it?

341
00:27:45,040 --> 00:27:47,360
 The gospel declares to us today,

342
00:27:47,360 --> 00:27:50,960
 in Christ, we can be bold and fearless.

343
00:27:50,960 --> 00:27:56,120
 (speaking in foreign language)

344
00:28:05,200 --> 00:28:09,120
 (speaking in foreign language)

345
00:28:09,120 --> 00:28:30,360
 Come to God right now,

346
00:28:30,360 --> 00:28:33,240
 no matter how much fear in your heart.

347
00:28:34,160 --> 00:28:36,920
 Quiet yourself and come boldly

348
00:28:36,920 --> 00:28:39,320
 to the throne of grace by faith.

349
00:28:39,320 --> 00:28:43,040
 Tell God all your burdens.

350
00:28:43,040 --> 00:28:46,880
 If you have conflict with a brother or sister,

351
00:28:46,880 --> 00:28:50,280
 take the initiative to seek reconciliation

352
00:28:50,280 --> 00:28:55,080
 so that the church can be a testimony of unity

353
00:28:55,080 --> 00:28:56,440
 in this divided world.

354
00:28:56,440 --> 00:28:59,960
 Stand firm in the midst of trials,

355
00:28:59,960 --> 00:29:03,240
 entrust the difficulties you are facing to God

356
00:29:03,240 --> 00:29:07,000
 and ask Lord to help you not lose heart,

357
00:29:07,000 --> 00:29:10,760
 but instead, see how even your suffering

358
00:29:10,760 --> 00:29:13,080
 can become God's glory.

359
00:29:13,080 --> 00:29:14,360
 (speaking in foreign language)

360
00:29:14,360 --> 00:29:15,200
 Let's pray.

361
00:29:15,200 --> 00:29:20,880
 (speaking in foreign language)

362
00:29:33,240 --> 00:29:37,160
 (speaking in foreign language)

363
00:29:37,160 --> 00:29:48,680
 - Heavenly Father, we are unworthy people,

364
00:29:48,680 --> 00:29:54,640
 but in Jesus Christ, you have opened a way for us.

365
00:29:54,640 --> 00:29:59,320
 Help us, please help us to look more to Christ

366
00:29:59,320 --> 00:30:02,040
 so that in our weakness and fear,

367
00:30:02,040 --> 00:30:04,280
 we may still come to you.

368
00:30:04,280 --> 00:30:07,960
 Help us to believe that you are sovereign,

369
00:30:07,960 --> 00:30:09,920
 even in trials.

370
00:30:09,920 --> 00:30:13,480
 Let the church become witness of unity

371
00:30:13,480 --> 00:30:15,240
 in this broken world.

372
00:30:15,240 --> 00:30:16,800
 In the name of Jesus.

